The survey area lies on the eastern edge of the{Berkshire Downs} which are arable uplands. Along the summit runs the ancient{Ridgeway,}used as a main trading route during the Bronze Age.
Woodlands are found on the higher ground due to the presence of a thin layer of clay-with-flints which holds water.
The{River Thames,}flowing north-south at this point has cut through this line of chalk hills at the famous{Goring Gap,}where the twin villages of{Goring and Streatley}lie on each river bank. Further east the hills continue as the{Chilterns.}
